President Cyril Ramaphosa has called for consolidated reports from his Cabinet as the country experiences rapidly rising coronavirus cases. PRETORIA - President Cyril Ramaphosa addressed the nation on Sunday evening outlining the measures South Africa is taking in dealing with the coronavirus. Ramaphosa's address comes after a special cabinet meeting to discuss measures to contain the spread of the virus. At least 61 people have been infected in South Africa. READ: Wits student tests positive for coronavirus All of them had travelled overseas. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.